title: For Sale/Trade:  CVA .45 (.440) Rifled Barrel flintlock built from kit never fired rifle.
postcontent: What I have for sale for $200 is a built from an early 1980's C.V.A. Kentucky Rifle/Hunter Flintlock kit model # KA706.  This is a nice octagonal 33.5 inch barrel that has never been shot.  Long story short my father received as a gift approx. in 1980/81 but my parents shortly divorced after receiving.  It was forgotten about for years tucked away in a closet til I inherited it a few years ago.  I built the kit but I never "got into" blackpowder shooting since I am only a modern firearms/military enthusiast.  It became a wall hanger only but need to make room and now I want to see it go to someone who will shoot and appreciate it.  From CVA this was a .45 caliber rifled barrel but shoots .440 ball ammo with a.015" patch,  I guess you do not shoot conicals or sabot's with these rifles.  All CVA side lock kit blackpowder firearms were discontinued over 15 years ago.  Deer Creek and Dixie Gun Works and Track of the Wolf have blackpowder items as do major retailers like Cabela's or Gander Mountain.  With this type you can make "fancier" and you may need re-finishing to your liking.  I am including a 2nd edition Black Powder Guide from 1976 that is very informative for the shooter including blackpowder history, etc.  Rifle is complete.  You just need flint, leather or lead wrapping for the flint and the powder and balls to be ready to shoot.  Barrel #is 045699.  I am asking $200 cash because it has never been fired, all sales are final.  I am also throwing in a tube of "Bore Butter".  I can travel within 50 mile radius of Green Bay to an agreed upon public meeting site for any transactions.  At this point I am not interested in shipping it.  I may consider trades if you tell me what firearm or firearm accessories or ammunition you have that would be an approximate equivalent value trade.

title: For Sale:  Savage 12 LRP (Long Range Precision) .243 Win - PRICE DROP
postcontent:
I have a gently used Savage 12 LRP chambered in .243 Win for sale. I have around 120 rounds through it; just enough to finish my load testing. Story is I went to school in the U.P. When I graduated I moved down to the Detroit area for my job and well... shooting here is pretty damn difficult. 

Gun has a 10x56 IOR Valdada scope. This is a fixed scope and not the illuminated version. Has the sun shade. Information can be seen here: http://www.valdada.com/10x56-30mm-tactical-scope-standard-mp-8-reticule/

Gun uses Seekins Precision rings and to be honest I don't remember anything about the base. But it's a standard base, no rise.

Also included is a harris bipod in the tilit version and a Boyt hard case with wheels which is very handy cause this is a heavy setup. 

With my hand loads, which are in the standard range of powder load for the bullet, I can achieve under 1/3 MOA at 100 yrds using the bipod and a sweatshirt as a rear rest. I'm really not that good of a shot... They say you might get lucky with a factory barrel and i think it's safe to say i got lucky. And this is using used brass and a lee reloading set. Not high dollar stuff folks.
